---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Lotus Rose Counseling in Orem, UT | Our Story"
  description="Learn about Lotus Rose Counseling — a therapy practice in Orem, Utah founded by Joy Bouchard, LCSW, specializing in trauma, postpartum, grief, and EMDR therapy."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <p class="section-label">Our Story</p>
      <h1>Why "Lotus Rose"?</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Two symbols of strength, resilience, and the ability to bloom after adversity.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Origin Story -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container">
        <h2>The Meaning Behind the Name</h2>
        <p>The lotus grows in muddy water and rises above the surface to bloom — a symbol of resilience, inner strength, and the ability to overcome life's most difficult moments.</p>
        <p>The rose represents rebirth, transformation, and personal growth. Together, these symbols capture what therapy is really about: not erasing the hard parts of your story, but growing through them into something stronger.</p>
        <p>That's the heart of Lotus Rose Counseling. We believe healing isn't about going back to who you were before. It's about moving forward — with new understanding, new tools, and a deeper connection to yourself.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container">
        <p class="section-label">What We Believe</p>
        <h2>Therapy That Meets You Where You Are</h2>
        <p>At Lotus Rose Counseling, we don't believe in one-size-fits-all therapy. Every person who walks through our door (or joins a telehealth session) brings a unique story, unique challenges, and unique strengths.</p>
        <p>Our therapists are trained in evidence-based modalities — EMDR, Accelerated Resolution Therapy, Internal Family Systems, Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, and more. But techniques are only part of the equation. The other part is the relationship.</p>

        <div class="highlight-box">
          <h4>Our Core Values</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>The therapeutic relationship is the foundation of healing</li>
            <li>Every client deserves a safe, nonjudgmental space</li>
            <li>Evidence-based approaches get real results</li>
            <li>Growth looks different for every person — and that's okay</li>
            <li>Healing is possible at any stage of life</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who We Serve -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container">
        <p class="section-label">Who We Work With</p>
        <h2>Women, Teens, and Children in Utah County</h2>
        <p>Our practice primarily serves women navigating life's most challenging moments — postpartum depression, trauma, grief, anxiety, relationship struggles, and identity transitions. We also work with teens and children dealing with behavioral challenges, anxiety, self-esteem issues, and trauma.</p>
        <p>Whether you're a new mom struggling with intrusive thoughts, a teenager navigating faith transitions, or a woman processing decades-old trauma — there's a therapist at Lotus Rose who understands your experience.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Space -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container text-center">
        <p class="section-label">Our Space</p>
        <h2>A Place That Feels Like Home</h2>
        <p>Our office is located in a cozy basement space under Forever by Ash in Orem. We intentionally designed every room to feel warm, inviting, and nothing like a clinical setting. Comfortable couches, soft lighting, and thoughtful touches — because the environment matters when you're doing vulnerable work.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <div class="photo-placeholder">Therapy Room</div>
        <div class="photo-placeholder">Waiting Area</div>
        <div class="photo-placeholder">Therapy Room</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Begin Your Healing Journey?</h2>
      <p>Schedule a free 15-minute consultation to find the right therapist for you.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">Schedule Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    background: var(--gradient-hero);
    padding: 100px 0 80px;
    text-align: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 30% 20%, rgba(255,255,255,0.4) 0%, transparent 60%);
  }
  .hero-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .hero h1 { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--text-medium);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .photo-placeholder {
    background: var(--gradient-hero);
    border-radius: 12px;
    height: 220px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--text-medium);
    font-size: 14px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
  }
  .photo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero { padding: 70px 0 60px; }
    .photo-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
